12/08/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Two trials for crimes against humanity, stemming from the conflicts in the former Yugoslavia, will be held this week, Tanjug reported on Sunday (August 12th). 
From Monday through Friday, the tribunal will hear the case against former Serbian Prime Minister Milan Milutinovic and five other indictees, charged with the deportation, murder and persecution of about 800,000 Kosovo Albanians in the first half of 1999.
The case against former BiH Foreign Minister Jadranko Prlic and five other Bosnian Croats accused of murder, torture, and persecution of Muslims in southeastern Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) during the 1992-1995 conflict has been scheduled for Thursday and Friday. 
(Tanjug - 12/08/07)
